<reference anchor="I-D.yc-v6ops-solicited-ra-unicast" target="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-yc-v6ops-solicited-ra-unicast-00">
  <front>
    <title>Sending Solicited RAs Unicast</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-yc-v6ops-solicited-ra-unicast-00"/>
    <author initials="A." surname="Yourtchenko" fullname="Andrew Yourtchenko"/>
    <author initials="L." surname="Colitti" fullname="Lorenzo Colitti"/>
    <date day="06" month="July" year="2015"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>On links with a large number of mobile devices, sending Solicited
   Router Advertisement as multicast packets can severely impact host
   power consumption.  This document recommends that on such network,
   RAs be sent unicast.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
</reference>